The paper discusses mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves optimization and linear programming (cs.DS), as well as machine learning and decision making (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of Dantzig-Wolfe decomposition and Benders decomposition also suggests a focus on mathematical programming and optimization (cs.CC).
